In article <114800@bu.edu> uni@acs.bu.edu (Shaen Bernhardt) writes:
>I'd love to hear some suggestions on automatic deletion applications.

Check out the manual for Norton's DISKREET. It has several mechanisms
for destroying the secret key used to encrypt a file system, including
a simple timeout and a "panic" feature (e.g., hitting both shift keys
at the same time). And of course, there's always turning off the power.

Phil
